In a {{ill|Western calendar|ja|иҘҝжҡҰ}} year whose final digit is 1 or 6 (when the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|еҚҒе№І}} are {{ill|Sin|ja|иҫӣ}} and {{ill|Hei|ja|дёҷ}}), the month of {{ill|July|ja|7жңҲ}} is designated as the Heishin month ({{ill|month (calendar)|ja|жңҲ (жҡҰ)}}). However, here the term "month" may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Old Calendar|ja|ж—§жҡҰ}} or to the seasonal month (from {{ill|Beginning of Autumn|ja|з«Ӣз§Ӣ}} until the day before {{ill|White Dew|ja|зҷҪйңІ}}) as applicable.

