In a {{ill|Western calendar|ja|иҘҝжҡҰ|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=иҘҝжҡҰ|4=zh|5=е…¬е…ғ|6=es|7=Era comГәn|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} year whose final digit is 1 or 6 (when the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|еҚҒе№І|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} are {{ill|Sin|ja|иҫӣ|1=Kanoto (иҫӣ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and {{ill|Hei|ja|дёҷ|1=Hinoe (дёҷ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}), the month of {{ill|July|ja|7жңҲ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} is designated as the Heishin month ({{ill|month (calendar)|ja|жңҲ (жҡҰ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}). However, here the term "month" may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Lunisolar|ja|ж—§жҡҰ|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} or to the seasonal month (from {{ill|Beginning of Autumn|ja|з«Ӣз§Ӣ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} until the day before {{ill|White Dew|ja|зҷҪйңІ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}) as applicable.

